The paper focuses on the control algorithm for connected and automated vehicles, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). The use of algorithms to build a lookup table and search for ideal control gains suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. Finally, the numerical simulation aspect of the study suggests the possibility of it being categorized under cs.MA (multi-agent systems).
